The paper discusses a game-theoretic approach to modeling social media interactions, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the category of cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). Additionally, the paper deals with social networks and communication graphs, which are common topics in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks). The use of algorithms to seek Nash equilibria also suggests a connection to cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
